summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions and statements on the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC),

Determining the situation in DRC continues to threaten international peace and security,

Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,

1. Reiterates measures in resolution 1807 (2008) applying to non-governmental entities and individuals in DRC;
2. Decides notification requirements in paragraph 5 of resolution 1807 (2008) shall no longer apply;
3. Requests DRC Government to report by 31 May 2023 on efforts to manage national stockpiles, fight arms trafficking and diversion;
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
